## Step 3 — Add the regression test script

From the repo root:

```bash
mkdir -p tests
```

Create:

```bash
vi tests/test-phase6.sh
```

Put this in it:

```bash
#!/usr/bin/env bash
set -euo pipefail

CID="${CID:-pxe-content}"
SCRIPT="${SCRIPT:-/usr/local/bin/generate-pxe-content.py}"
BASE_URL="${BASE_URL:-http://127.0.0.1:18080}"

echo "== Phase 6 regression test =="

echo "-- Python syntax check"
podman exec "$CID" python3 -m py_compile "$SCRIPT"

echo "-- Generate once"
podman exec "$CID" python3 "$SCRIPT" --once

echo "-- Fetch generated files"
curl -fss "$BASE_URL/boot.ipxe" -o /tmp/boot.ipxe
curl -fss "$BASE_URL/index.html" -o /tmp/index.html
curl -fss "$BASE_URL/generated/status.json" -o /tmp/status.json
curl -fss "$BASE_URL/ks/rhel8-minimal.ks" -o /tmp/rhel8-minimal.ks

echo "-- Validate status JSON"
python3 -m json.tool /tmp/status.json >/dev/null

echo "-- Confirm Jinja includes rendered away"
if grep -Eq '\{% include|partials/' /tmp/rhel8-minimal.ks; then
  echo "ERROR: Jinja include remained in generated kickstart"
  exit 1
fi

echo "-- Confirm core Kickstart content exists"
grep -q 'url --url=' /tmp/rhel8-minimal.ks
grep -q 'rootpw --iscrypted' /tmp/rhel8-minimal.ks
grep -q '@^minimal-environment' /tmp/rhel8-minimal.ks

echo "-- Confirm Phase 6 status/index visibility"
grep -q '"generator"' /tmp/status.json
grep -q '"active_overrides"' /tmp/status.json
grep -q '"stale_kickstarts"' /tmp/status.json
grep -q 'Generation Policy' /tmp/index.html
grep -q 'Kickstart State' /tmp/index.html
grep -q 'Warnings' /tmp/index.html
grep -q 'Generated Files' /tmp/index.html

echo "-- Confirm root password hash is not leaked into status/index"
if grep -E '\$6\$|REKKqe02' /tmp/status.json /tmp/index.html; then
  echo "ERROR: root password hash leaked into status/index"
  exit 1
fi

echo "-- Confirm future placeholders do not generate real boot targets"
if grep -Eq 'inst\.ks=.*(developer-workstation|security-baseline|security-luks|embedded-edge)' /tmp/boot.ipxe; then
  echo "ERROR: future placeholder profile generated a real boot target"
  exit 1
fi

echo "PASS: Phase 6 regression test passed"
```

Then make it executable:

```bash
chmod +x tests/test-phase6.sh
```

---

## Step 4 — Run the test

After your image/container is rebuilt with the current Python file, run this from the repo root:

```bash
CID=pxe-content ./tests/test-phase6.sh
```

You want:

```text
PASS: Phase 6 regression test passed
```

If your container name is different, change `CID`:

```bash
CID=my-container-name ./tests/test-phase6.sh
```

If your port is different:

```bash
CID=pxe-content BASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:18080 ./tests/test-phase6.sh
```

## Bottom line

For 6E, you are adding:

```text
examples/overrides/profiles/10-minimal-override.example.yml
examples/overrides/templates/ks/rhel8-minimal.example.ks.j2
tests/test-phase6.sh
```

You are **not** editing the Python file unless the test fails.
